grepai is a privacy-first semantic code search tool.

Unlike grep (exact text matching), grepai indexes the meaning of your code
using vector embeddings, enabling natural language searches.

It runs as a background daemon, maintaining a real-time "mental map" of your
project to serve as reliable context for developers and AI agents.

Usage:
  grepai [command]

Available Commands:
  agent-setup Configure AI agents to use grepai
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  help        Help about any command
  init        Initialize grepai in the current directory
  mcp-serve   Start grepai as an MCP server
  search      Search codebase with natural language
  status      Display index status and browse indexed files
  trace       Trace symbol callers and callees
  update      Update grepai to the latest version
  version     Print version information
  watch       Start the real-time file watcher daemon

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for grepai

Use "grepai [command] --help" for more information about a command.
